prompt:
Fix crostini home-manager configuration to support multiple usernames across different machines.

## Changes needed

### 1. flake.nix (homeConfigurations section)
Replace the single 'crostini' output with two per-user outputs:

```nix
# Remove this:
"crostini" = mkHome {
  username = "patrick";
  identity = ./home/identities/personal.nix;
  baseModule = ./home/crostini.nix;
};

# Add these:
"patrick@crostini" = mkHome {
  username = "patrick";
  identity = ./home/identities/personal.nix;
  baseModule = ./home/crostini.nix;
};

"paflynn@crostini" = mkHome {
  username = "paflynn";
  identity = ./home/identities/work.nix;
  baseModule = ./home/crostini.nix;
};
```

### 2. home/crostini.nix
The update and rebuild aliases should use 'nix run home-manager/master --' instead of bare 'home-manager' since home-manager may not be on PATH before first activation:

```nix
update = lib.mkForce "nix run home-manager/master -- switch --flake github:patflynn/cosmo#${config.home.username}@crostini";
rebuild = lib.mkForce "nix run home-manager/master -- switch --flake .#${config.home.username}@crostini";
```

### 3. CI (.github/workflows/ci.yml)
Update the home configurations matrix to replace 'crostini' with 'patrick@crostini' and 'paflynn@crostini'.

### 4. docs/crostini-setup.md
Update any references to the old flake output name.

Make sure nixfmt passes and CI config is correct.
